    "body": "Yarn PnP doesn't extract packages to the `node_modules` directory, but serves them directly from the `.tgz` sort of at runtime. Tools need to be changed to support this, for example Truffle and the OpenZeppelin CLI would need to know to look for contracts in the PnP \"repository\" rather than in `node_modules`.\r\n\r\nEthPM would also not put contracts in `node_modules`, though, so unless the tooling already supports that the situation is not so different. Implementing support for EthPM in tools sounds easier and less controversial, though.",
